reviews.review_text: Amazing! Holy shit! Fabulous sound... Easy Wind... Lovin the gnarley biker sound. Commercial release? Please? Pretty please?

The GRATEFUL DEAD "Live On Stage" at the Manhattan Center, New York City, New York, United States of America `

~^|\_@|@_/|^~
~<->/<->\<->~

Superduper 71'Soundboard.

April 1971....my favorite GRATEFUL DEAD of all time.

There is nothing like a GRATEFUL DEAD show with Pigpen.

Five stars for the mix, recording, performance, transfer, & "dance-ability".

NYC crowds 'LOVED' Pigpen and they still do.

I highly recommend adding this NYC show to your 1971 GRATEFUL DEAD collection. 

It's a "Gotta Have It, Must Have" show. 

NYC crowds always brought out the best in the GRATEFUL DEAD.

Solid, "In the Pocket" performances of all our favorite 71' songs. 

I recommend using your EQ during playback of most of the shows on the IA, this one included. Windows Media Player has a 10 band EQ and SRS WOW effects that enhance the sound.

GEMS does it again...an "Audio Masterpiece". We all appreciate and love you for you hard work.

Here's one way to download this show:

The IA recommends users of Windows XP view this web-page with RealPlayer.

RealPlayer is a free media player you can download at www.realplayer.com. 

Using RealPlayer to view this webpage, click the VBR M3U link to open the songs in the Playlist. If your Playlist is not open, open it by clicking the Playlist icon at the lower right hand corner of RealPlayer. 

Once the songs are in the Playlist, double click the song to play it, then click the record button at the lower left hand corner of Realplayer to record it. 

When the red line reaches the other end click the stop button to download the song. Your song is in the RealPlayer Downloads folder. Repeat these steps for each song.

Eat, Drink, Be Merry and Listen to the GRATEFUL DEAD.

Thanks for the LOVE from 1971.

EASY EASY EASY of coarse we all have our own system when it comes to tagging certain versions of dead songs as "the best", and im usually not one to do so (nor do i post often), but this version of Easy Wind is by far the absolute best! Psychedelic Grateful Dead Blues as its FINEST! and notice that at the end of the jam they bring it all back to that slow, nitty-gritty blues in an almost flawless fashion.  Thank you Pig Pen

oh uh um ha:  any time i see you comment on a show ('70-'74), i know its worth a (full) listen.  



"but hey, then again I wasn't there"

Microcosmic This show like the year is a bit uneven. Phil is up front and doing his thing. But the overall vibe is pretty mellow.  These shows were recorded on 16 track, it's not surprising that none of them have been officially released.

1971 dead at their best This performance  has versions of particular songs that are my kind of GD. Loser is awsesome, It is intense. Easy Wind is great..phil with that hollow bass ,Pigpen with his b3 Hammond ,naturally produce a very unique overall sound that the dead had in '71 and is very pronounced throughout this show.
